	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=61546><span id=Sage>Slipskin</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>1056 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.44]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Frankly, playing the bard to level 20 does not give the best feel.&nbsp;&nbsp;As the songs change the tactics change.  My bard is level 22 now. I use the same tactics with him as I have for a long time - pull with BBB, fire up JWW, and now, instead of HoR I rotate in LMB unless I get a lot of resists or my health goes below 50%.  I still fight with weapons and not instruments (got a nice deal on Icetooth Claws and Phosphorecent Fiber). For armor I have Fine Steel Plate all around (did a lot of harvesting of of silks and pelts for a smith friend plus cashed in a lot of greater lightstones). <br><br>When I hit 26 and get AAS I expect to change tactics to fear kiting.  Then, when I get to 27 I will try charm kiting.  I may even switch to instruments only at that point.  <br><br>Grouping is a whole different art.  Different songs.  It depends on the make up of the group and what my main role is.  Mostly, I have been back up tank and mana battery. So, CCC and LMB make up most of my playing time.  During long down times (rare in Paludal Caverns) I even get out the mandolin and do HoR if needed.<br><br>So, starting out a low level bard with uber gear may not be the best use of your money.  Play the bard. See how you like it.  Get some lower level and mid level gear until 30.  Then get him tweaked out if you plan to keep playing him.</p>&nbsp;<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222</a><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760</a></td></td></tr>
