	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=145143><span id=Scholar>wolas</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>27 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>The size of you mana pool does not matter really. You will always have enough for charming.<br><br>The trouble with mana and bard (and its not a trouble its intentional) is the regen rate of this mana. It is slow and NOTHING can speed it up.<br><br>So NEVER bother with wis / int / mana.<br><br>Concentrate on DEX STA AGI STR and CHA<br>DEX to reduce missed notes<br>STA to have more hps and to be able to fight longer<br>AGI to increase your defense (you ll need it when you will do crowd control)<br>STR is obvious for damage<br>CHA for charming and mezzing<br></p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
