	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=4&mid=102814098015909>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=102814098015909>RE: Macro's and Bards</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=102814098015909#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, Jul 31st 2:56 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=60483><span id=Scholar>Polyflame</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>19 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Heres what my bard has for macros:<br><br>Slot 1:&nbsp;&nbsp;Special Attack.  Basicly this macro makes you attack, and do 3 other commands at once.  This is a good macro for just about any melee class.<br>/attack off (Stops your attack)<br>/doability 1 (That would be something like beg or sense heading)<br>/doability 2 (That would be something else like doability 1)<br>/doability 7 (That would be Instill doubt, or change it to doability 3 if you want a normal skill.)<br>/attack on (Makes you attack)<br><br>Slot 2:  General slot 1.  It's just an empty slot in your inventory with no bag or anything on it.<br><br>Slot 3:  General slot 2.  This is another inventory slot, but with an instrument like drums or strings.<br><br>Slot 4:  General slot 3.  Same as slot 2.<br><br>Slot 5:  Primary melee slot.  Its your primary weapon slot.<br><br>Slot 6:  Secondary melee slot.  Its your secondary weapon slot.<br><br>Slot 7:  Song macro.  This is pretty cool, it lets you twist a bunch of songs with the click of a button.<br>/stopsong (Stops your current song)<br>/cast 1 (Casts your first song, best if a melee song)<br>/pause 30 (Pauses for 3 seconds)<br>/stopsong (You know what it does by now)<br>/cast 2 (Plays your second song)<br><br>Slot 8:  The second song macro.  This finishes off your song macros, and lets you twist 4 at once with ease.<br>/stopsong (Duh)<br>/cast 3 (Duh again)<br>/pause 30 (I shouldnt have to do this)<br>/stopsong (Dum de dum...)<br>/cast 4 (Voila!)<br><br>Slot 9:  Whatever you want, preferably the Forage skill.<br><br>Slot 10:  Whatever you want again.<br><br>Aaaaand there you have it my musical friends, macros for a bard.  You can replace slot 9 or 10 with another instrument slot if you wish.<br><br>Hope this helps, good luckest to thou =).</p>&nbsp;<br>~Sloree<br>Nameless server<br>Level 46 Human Monk</td></td></tr>
