	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=69206><span id= >dimle</span></a><br><span id=notbold>50 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [1.80]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Excuse me for butting in with what I think is the answer to the question, but by Melee 1, he means your primary melee slot, the one where you usually stick your sword when you fight; melee 2 would in your early years be the one where you mount your shield when you fight (and use for your secondary weapon in late years.)<br><br>The idea is to basically get your primary and secondary melee slots, and the slots you use for your instrument inventory, plus an empty one, all showing up on your hotkeys.&nbsp;&nbsp;Sounds difficult to explain, but is simple to do once you get the idea.</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
