	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=174788><span id= >Perotinus</span></a><br><span id=notbold>6 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>The first significant quests you should do are the Songweaver Quests.<br><br>The armor quests are listed as lvls 5-8 but most of the items you need will more than likely be on EC vendors to save you time.&nbsp;&nbsp;It has slightly lower AC than banded and lots of great modifiers.  I did this at lvl 18 and I'm not giving it up until I get my lambent.<br><br>(One note on the armor: You collect the items and make them in a forge, but you don't need to have any smithing skills.)<br><br>Once you've done the armor, you're offered a quest where you turn in beads from three named orcs in EC.  This is for a good lowbie sword.<br><br>Here's the catch: To get the breastplate for the armor, you need to get two items from wisps which can't be hit with non-magical weapons.  Therefore, you might try to see if you can do the Songweaver Sword quest first.<br><br>Good luck!<br><br>Perotinus Forte<br>- Bard of the 20th Song</p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
